1
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:39,950
[The Story of Xing Fu]

2
00:01:40,050 --> 00:01:42,950
[Episode 35]

3
00:01:43,599 --> 00:01:44,239
Lawyers,

4
00:01:44,239 --> 00:01:45,280
you are finally here.

5
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:46,079
Look.

6
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:48,239
These are all the documents on my son's illness.

7
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,719
It's only been slightly over two years

8
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:52,840
after the opening
of the health products factory.

9
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,280
My son has been falling sick after that.

10
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,719
His temperament changed greatly.

11
00:01:55,959 --> 00:01:57,879
Every now and then, he has headaches,

12
00:01:57,879 --> 00:01:58,959
stomachaches,

13
00:01:59,519 --> 00:02:00,799
and diarrhea.

14
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,159
The hospital gave him drips.

15
00:02:03,799 --> 00:02:05,239
He was okay at times but sick again.

16
00:02:05,239 --> 00:02:06,879
I don't know what to do.

17
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,120
My wife has cancer

18
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:09,959
and spent more than 400,000 yuan.

19
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:11,760
She has had a relapse lately

20
00:02:12,159 --> 00:02:12,959
and needs surgery,

21
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:14,640
radiotherapy, and chemotherapy.

22
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,799
Where am I going to get the money?

23
00:02:17,879 --> 00:02:19,560
Now she can only wait to die.

24
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,599
What can we do?

25
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,120
It's been more than five years.

26
00:02:26,159 --> 00:02:26,680
Wait.

27
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:28,039
You said she fell sick

28
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:29,319
five years ago.

29
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:31,879
When did Wan Village

30
00:02:32,479 --> 00:02:34,319
start the health products factory?

31
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:35,639
Three years ago.

32
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:42,520
Folks,

33
00:02:43,879 --> 00:02:44,800
we are here today

34
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,639
because of the pollution in Shuiwei Village

35
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:49,080
caused by the Wan Village's
health products factory

36
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,080
that has sickened people.

37
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,159
Therefore,

38
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:56,000
if you got sick before the factory
started production,

39
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,719
you would not be

40
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:59,080
on the consultation list.

41
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,840
I hope you understand that.

42
00:03:01,159 --> 00:03:02,919
She got worse after the factory started.

43
00:03:03,199 --> 00:03:03,919
Yes.

44
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:04,800
Mr. Lawyer,

45
00:03:05,199 --> 00:03:06,159
my kid

46
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,639
got sick in the last two years.

47
00:03:07,879 --> 00:03:09,280
All of them can testify for me.

48
00:03:10,199 --> 00:03:11,000
This kid

49
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:13,039
kept having colds and fevers lately

50
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:15,080
and complaining about stomachaches.

51
00:03:15,479 --> 00:03:15,879
So,

52
00:03:16,479 --> 00:03:18,000
aren't those people from Wan Village

53
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,479
unscrupulous?

54
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:20,680
They only want to make money.

55
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:22,479
It's good that you are here now.

56
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,800
You must help us

57
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,080
get our compensation.

58
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,319
Yes. Make them pay.

59
00:03:26,319 --> 00:03:27,199
Help us.

60
00:03:27,919 --> 00:03:28,680
Folks,

61
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:30,719
we are

62
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:31,960
lawyers.

63
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,639
Like you,

64
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,240
we don't have

65
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,080
the authority.

66
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:38,439
Like you,

67
00:03:38,879 --> 00:03:39,800
we also have

68
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:42,080
a very powerful weapon,

69
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,240
which are laws.

70
00:03:44,039 --> 00:03:45,360
Laws can protect

71
00:03:45,759 --> 00:03:46,639
you and me.

72
00:03:47,159 --> 00:03:48,639
They can also protect your children.

73
00:03:48,759 --> 00:03:50,759
If you have

74
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:52,759
legal claims on this issue,

75
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:56,159
you can give us the power of attorney.

76
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,680
We can represent you

77
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:59,039
to file a lawsuit in court.

78
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:00,840
However,

79
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,319
sir,

80
00:04:02,439 --> 00:04:04,120
our families

81
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,599
are not rich.

82
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,280
I owed a lot of money these few years

83
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,240
for my kid's treatment.

84
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,840
We do not have the money

85
00:04:10,159 --> 00:04:10,759
to hire you

86
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,759
for the lawsuit.

87
00:04:13,199 --> 00:04:14,560
That's right.

88
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,479
We don't have money.

89
00:04:15,479 --> 00:04:15,840
Yes.

90
00:04:18,319 --> 00:04:20,000
Don't worry about money.

91
00:04:20,479 --> 00:04:21,560
You don't have to pay

92
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,960
until we win the case.

93
00:04:24,759 --> 00:04:26,199
The fee will be five percent

94
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:27,120
of the compensation.

95
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:29,000
Folks,

96
00:04:29,759 --> 00:04:30,519
listen.

97
00:04:31,279 --> 00:04:32,480
There is a more worrying

98
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,560
matter

99
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,680
than the attorney fee.

100
00:04:34,959 --> 00:04:38,120
We can't guarantee that we will win the lawsuit.

101
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:40,240
This is about evidence.

102
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,480
More importantly,

103
00:04:41,839 --> 00:04:43,680
the litigation process is very long.

104
00:04:44,079 --> 00:04:46,079
During this time, many unexpected problems

105
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,800
can occur.

106
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:50,519
For example, the other party
may sabotage our lawsuit

107
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,800
and divide you,

108
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:53,680
bribe you,

109
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,399
or threaten you.

110
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,399
As lawyers,

111
00:04:56,079 --> 00:04:57,399
we are afraid that the litigants

112
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,800
may secretly take bribes

113
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:01,079
without the lawyers' knowledge.

114
00:05:01,519 --> 00:05:02,199
That will

115
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:03,160
seriously undermine

116
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,720
the lawsuit.

117
00:05:05,319 --> 00:05:06,759
If that happens,

118
00:05:06,759 --> 00:05:08,279
we can't fight for the best interest

119
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:09,519
of our litigants.

120
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,480
Folks,

121
00:05:12,199 --> 00:05:13,240
a lawsuit

122
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,279
isn't child's play.

123
00:05:14,959 --> 00:05:16,000
It isn't something you can take lightly.

124
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,639
After you've thought it through,

125
00:05:18,199 --> 00:05:18,680
we'll

126
00:05:18,959 --> 00:05:19,800
help you in the court of law.

127
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,319
If you're hesitant,

128
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,120
then I suggest

129
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,800
that you don't file first.

130
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:27,480
Do you understand?

131
00:05:28,639 --> 00:05:29,560
Lawyers,

132
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,120
I wish to state my position.

133
00:05:31,399 --> 00:05:33,040
I definitely want to file the lawsuit.

134
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:34,680
I'll persevere.

135
00:05:34,759 --> 00:05:36,120
I wish to state my position too.

136
00:05:37,079 --> 00:05:39,240
They've hurt my child.

137
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:41,800
I have nowhere to retreat.

138
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,040
Sir,

139
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,399
just handle the case.

140
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:51,360
It's not something that I can just handle.

141
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:51,920
Let us

142
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,279
discuss this.

143
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,560
Please give us a moment.

144
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,319
What do you think?

145
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,959
Should we sign?

146
00:06:01,959 --> 00:06:02,879
If we want to sign,

147
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,199
we should call Qin

148
00:06:04,199 --> 00:06:06,519
to draw up an agreement and send it to us
as soon as possible.

149
00:06:07,199 --> 00:06:08,519
I think we shouldn't rush it

150
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:09,879
as if we have motives.

151
00:06:10,079 --> 00:06:12,000
After all, such a lawsuit is a thankless job.

152
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,120
What about you?

153
00:06:13,399 --> 00:06:14,240
I think so too.

154
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,600
Mainly, I think

155
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,959
we should give them some time.

156
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,480
Let them go back, think about it,

157
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,240
and discuss with their families

158
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,240
before

159
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:22,360
deciding.

160
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:23,639
Okay.

161
00:06:24,079 --> 00:06:24,639
We'll wait and see.

162
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:27,839
Folks,

163
00:06:28,959 --> 00:06:30,360
thank you for trusting us.

164
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:32,279
Well,

165
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,759
everyone should go back and think about it.

166
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,879
Discuss with your family members.

167
00:06:37,079 --> 00:06:38,199
After that,

168
00:06:38,399 --> 00:06:40,000
we can sign the proxy agreement.

169
00:06:40,199 --> 00:06:40,920
Okay?

170
00:06:42,519 --> 00:06:43,199
Okay.

171
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,639
We'll do as you say.

172
00:06:45,639 --> 00:06:47,199
Why is it dragging on?

173
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:48,959
Poverty must've made them crazy.

174
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,319
They got lawyers.

175
00:06:50,879 --> 00:06:51,800
What do they want?

176
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,079
What do you think?

177
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,519
You're the general manager.

178
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,000
You should know.

179
00:06:57,319 --> 00:06:58,079
Look.

180
00:06:58,079 --> 00:06:59,120
I'm busy every day.

181
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,120
Busy doing what?

182
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,279
Are you as busy as me?

183
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,680
You were busy giving me trouble.

184
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:10,319
Well,

185
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,000
is the equipment always on?

186
00:07:14,879 --> 00:07:16,199
Yes.

187
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,800
Mo, let me tell you.

188
00:07:19,279 --> 00:07:20,319
This is a big deal.

189
00:07:20,439 --> 00:07:21,600
Don't you try to fool me.

190
00:07:24,879 --> 00:07:26,000
Mr. Wan,

191
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,959
don't worry. It's switched on.

192
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,120
Okay.

193
00:07:32,199 --> 00:07:34,079
I heard they got
the Ministry of Ecology and Environment

194
00:07:34,279 --> 00:07:35,720
to do a water assessment.

195
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,199
The Ministry?

196
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:45,399
Even if the water is bad,

197
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,800
we have nothing to do with it.

198
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,240
They want a big company to pay.

199
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,240
Ignore them.

200
00:07:49,879 --> 00:07:51,319
I want to do that,

201
00:07:51,759 --> 00:07:53,040
but I'm worried.

202
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,959
I heard that many families

203
00:07:55,959 --> 00:07:56,920
have fallen sick.

204
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,519
They want a lawsuit against us.

205
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,360
We should get ready.

206
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,279
I'll call the lawyer.

207
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:05,560
Who?

208
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,680
He Xingyun.

209
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,439
Don't.

210
00:08:07,959 --> 00:08:09,079
I think

211
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:11,000
you should call

212
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,800
Mr. Han about this issue.

213
00:08:13,959 --> 00:08:14,759
Ms. He

214
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,360
only cites legal articles

215
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,240
and always lectures me about laws.

216
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,480
She is annoying.

217
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,519
Mr. Han

218
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,160
is more experienced.

219
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:26,639
I think

220
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:27,800
you should discuss it with him.

221
00:08:38,439 --> 00:08:39,000
Mr. Han,

222
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:41,279
I need your consultation.

223
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:52,759
It isn't that complicated.

224
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:54,799
Mr. Wan,

225
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:57,559
isn't Ms. He your legal counsel?

226
00:08:57,759 --> 00:08:58,960
Why don't you ask her?

227
00:08:59,759 --> 00:09:01,320
It stands to reason that she should

228
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,279
provide legal consultation services.

229
00:09:04,279 --> 00:09:06,600
Okay. Let's drop the pretension.

230
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,480
I still want you to take care of this.

231
00:09:10,639 --> 00:09:11,240
How about this?

232
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:13,360
Drop by here.

233
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,120
Let's meet and talk in detail.

234
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,480
Okay. No problem.

235
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,639
I'll arrange it.

236
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:23,200
Ms. He and I will go there as soon as possible.

237
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,200
As soon as possible.

238
00:09:25,519 --> 00:09:26,080
Yes.

239
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,559
We more or less understand the situation.

240
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,279
Mr. Wan and Mr. Mo,

241
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,279
presently

242
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,600
our country

243
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,200
always attaches importance

244
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,759
to environmental protection issues.

245
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:45,679
Some judicial documents
were promulgated recently

246
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,320
that repeatedly emphasized this.

247
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:48,799
Yes, He,

248
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,360
explain the relevant legal provisions

249
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,120
to them.

250
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,039
Keep it simple.

251
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,519
It's like this.

252
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,000
First,

253
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:00,080
the "Tort Law of the People's Republic of China"

254
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:02,039
took effect in 2010.

255
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,679
Article 66 stipulates

256
00:10:04,519 --> 00:10:07,120
that for disputes arising
from pollution of the environment,

257
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:09,440
the polluter shall bear the burden of providing

258
00:10:09,519 --> 00:10:12,559
non-liability or diminished liability
in accordance with the provisions

259
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:14,639
of the law and the non-existence

260
00:10:14,639 --> 00:10:16,320
of a causal relationship between

261
00:10:16,559 --> 00:10:17,720
their actions and the damage.

262
00:10:17,919 --> 00:10:18,639
In 2015,

263
00:10:19,039 --> 00:10:19,840
in the "Interpretation of

264
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:22,360
the Supreme People's Court
of Several Issues on the Application of Law

265
00:10:22,559 --> 00:10:24,639
in the Trial of Disputes
over Liability for Environmental Torts",

266
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:25,879
Article One states

267
00:10:26,279 --> 00:10:27,799
that in the damages
caused by environmental pollution,

268
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,759
whether or not the polluter is at fault,

269
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:32,320
the polluter shall bear the tort liability.

270
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:35,120
If the polluter complies with the state or local

271
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:37,399
pollution discharge standards

272
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:38,919
and claims no responsibility,

273
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:41,159
the people's court won't support it.

274
00:10:42,039 --> 00:10:42,759
Therefore,

275
00:10:42,759 --> 00:10:45,480
it is very hard to fight a pollution lawsuit.

276
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:47,960
I think

277
00:10:49,559 --> 00:10:51,000
if we can persuade people,

278
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,279
try your best not to take it to court.

279
00:10:53,799 --> 00:10:54,919
If you have to,

280
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,840
don't make it a class action.

281
00:10:57,679 --> 00:10:58,679
After all,

282
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:00,440
with many people getting sick,

283
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:02,840
a judge might suspect

284
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:06,440
if it is due to some special reasons.

285
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,240
Although we have solid evidence,

286
00:11:10,519 --> 00:11:12,879
there still will be negative effects,

287
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,159
especially now that I hear

288
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,399
that Wan Village

289
00:11:17,799 --> 00:11:19,000
is a participant in a national

290
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,039
Entrepreneurship
in Rural Communities Competition.

291
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:22,320
Correct?

292
00:11:23,159 --> 00:11:25,759
It's better to be cautious
at this critical moment.

293
00:11:27,879 --> 00:11:29,559
If we don't want to take it to court,

294
00:11:30,039 --> 00:11:31,440
